page.title: 10A BABY IN GENERAL
page.content: James has changed in many ways, he has lost his chubbiness. He has a way of turning people on with his smile, he sort of creases his nose,mouth and eyes all in one. When he walks he totters a bit and sometimes falls over, but he only smiles and pulls himself up. He is very curious and very adventurous. He loves being cuddled and he also likes being the centre of attraction. James has a fancy for biscuits and knows in which cupboard they are kept. James knows simple commands like'pattacake', 'wave' and when you say "where's the baby?" He sometimes looks up at the photograph of himself. If you say his name he will immediately turn and look.
